# Internal governance memory -- confirmed never tracked at HEAD (`git
# ls-files -- MEMORY/` returned empty, 2026-07-21). Session state/decision
# logs stay local; the exposure check found these files necessarily name
# sensitive due-diligence findings (e.g. a redacted comparison-mark's
# identity) when explaining what was redacted and why -- that's correct
# for an internal audit trail but wrong for public history. NOTE: this
# does NOT extend to session-logs/ or NEXT-SESSION-*-STARTING-PROMPT.md --
# both have substantial pre-existing tracked history (9 and 7 files
# respectively, confirmed via `git ls-files` the same session) and a
# blanket gitignore there would split old-public/new-private inconsistently.
# That is a separate, deliberate decision, not made this session -- see
# MEMORY/critical-actions.md, 2026-07-21 entry.
MEMORY/

# Live internal progress dashboard -- Q1 decision, 2026-07-21 (see
# MEMORY/critical-actions.md): this file catalogues current weaknesses
# (MRR, paying-org count, every milestone's PAUSED/MISSING status) in one
# place and was never tracked at HEAD (git ls-files confirmed empty), so
# this is a clean gitignore with no history to split. A separate curated
# public-status document may be published later if a public progress
# signal is wanted; this raw dashboard stays internal-only.
PROGRESS.md
